The IEC also addressed issues surrounding the quality of the indelible ink used in this year's elections. People on social media came out complaining that the ink came out easily. Mamabolo said that an investigation that will be done in conjunction with the Council for Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR). Janet Love, the IEC's Deputy Chief Electoral Commissioner said that they looked at digitising the electoral system. She said however at the moment it is not something they think they'll be to implement. She also dismissed allegations of meddling by any power Russia or otherwise. https://twitter.com/Mbiizozo/status/1126465407047675905